In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or app builder configuration):

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // runs when app is paused
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // runs when app is stopped
        }));
#elif IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // runs when app enters background
        }));
#endif
});
```

Make sure you have:
```csharp
using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;
```

This registers handlers directly on the native platform events without needing custom platform code or renderers. You can chain multiple events (`.OnResume()`, `.WillTerminate()`, etc.) in the same builder block.
